1. PROJECT DOCUMENTATION


1.1 Project Title

AirFly Smart Delay Prediction System


1.2 Introduction

The AirFly Smart Delay Prediction System is a data-driven application designed to analyze historical airline data and predict flight delays using machine learning. It provides insights into delay patterns and helps users make better travel decisions.


1.3 Objectives

Analyze historical flight delay data

Identify major causes of delays

Build predictive models for delay classification

Provide interactive visualizations using Streamlit


1.4 Scope

The system focuses on:

Flight delay analysis

Machine learning prediction

Interactive dashboard visualization


Limitations:

Uses historical dataset only

No real-time API integration


1.5 Technology Stack


Frontend: Streamlit

Backend: Python

Libraries: Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn

Machine Learning: Scikit-learn

Models: Logistic Regression, Random Forest


1.6 System Architecture


Data Collection (CSV dataset)

Data Preprocessing

Feature Engineering

Model Training

Dashboard Visualization

Prediction System


1.7 Modules Description


🔐 Authentication Module

Simple signup/login using session state

📊 Dashboard Module

Visualizes delay patterns

Shows charts and insights

🤖 Model Module

Trains ML models

Compares accuracy

🔮 Prediction Module

Takes user input

Predicts delay probability

💬 Feedback Module

Collects user feedback

1.8 Dataset Description


Departure Date

Arrival Delay

Weather Delay

NAS Delay

Carrier Delay

Airport Name

Arrival Airport


1.9 Methodology

Data Cleaning

Feature Selection

Train-Test Split

Model Training

Evaluation using accuracy & confusion matrix


1.10 Results

Random Forest performed better than Logistic Regression

Key delay factors: Carrier Delay, NAS Delay

Dashboard provides clear insights


1.11 Conclusion

The system successfully predicts flight delays and provides useful insights. It helps users understand delay patterns and supports data-driven decision-making.


1.12 Future Enhancements

Real-time flight tracking

Advanced ML models (XGBoost, Deep Learning)

Mobile-friendly UI